race.comment: MYSTERY 'N' DRAMA (9) looks a good each-way play to kick off the delayed meeting. Two runs back this time in have been good, beaten narrowly at Geelong in each. Put up a decent figure when third last time and that has her firmly in the mix. North of 20-1 available in early betting seems generous. SOMERSAULT (11) is another at an early double-figure quote who has claims. She was just ahead of MYSTERY 'N' DRAMA when they met and has been good again since. She draws for every chance. MISSAPPREHEND (8) ran on well late with the tempo against as a beaten favourite when last seen at Cranbourne. She draws to sit closer now and profiles well. PHINEAS (2) ran well fresh at Sale and should be fitter now. MISS MARANDA (7) maps for a soft run behind the leaders and has claims in an open race.
